                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                                                                                <tr class='spec_recom gradeI'>
                                <td>Asymptomatic adolescents and adults</td>
                                <td>The USPSTF concludes that the current evidence is insufficient to assess the balance of benefits and harms of visual skin examination by a clinician to screen for skin cancer in adolescents and adults.

See the Practice Considerations section for additional information regarding the I statement.</td> 
                                <td><span class='gradeI'> I</span></td> 
                            </tr>
